  "Sanction Details" : "DECISION RENDERED JULY 6, 2001 WHEREIN RESPONDENT SPINDEL IS FINED $2,500 PLUS A TOTAL OF $3,966.58 IN COSTS. IF NO FURTHER ACTION, DECISION IS FINAL AUGUST 23, 2001. ** AUGUST 23, 2001 - DECISION FINAL.",
  "Broker Comment" : "APPLICANT WAS FOUND LIABLE UNDER RULE 2110 AND WAS FINED $2,500 PLUS COSTS.  APPLICANT WAS NOT CENSURED.  THE HEARING PANEL FOUND \"SEVERAL MITIGATING CIRCUMSTANCES\".  IT INDICATED THAT APPLICANT'S \"ARRANGEMENT FOR  LIMITED OVERSIGHT...WAS REASONABLE WHEN IT WAS ADOPTED, CONSIDERING THE FIRM'S HISTORY, NATURE AND PERSONNEL\".   IT RECOGNIZED THAT THE HIGH QUALITY-HIGH LIQUIDITY SECURITIES \"ACQUISITIONS, WHICH LED TO ... NET CAPITAL DEFICIENCIES,  REPRESENTED A SIGNIFICANT DEPARTURE FROM THE FIRM'S HISTORIC TRADING PATTERN\".  IT STATED FURTHER THAT \"THERE IS NO SUGGESTION THAT SPINDEL INTENTIONALLY ALLOWED MERRION (OR ANY OTHER CLIENT) TO OPERATE IN NET CAPITAL  DEFICIENCY...\".    THOUGH THE HEARING PANEL HAS DECIDED THAT APPLICANT IS LIABLE, HE REMAINS TOTALLY CONVINCED OF HIS INNOCENCE IN THIS MATTER.  RATHER THAN CONTINUE TO EXPEND INORDINATE AMOUNTS OF TIME AND MONEY AND IN CONSIDERATION OF THE PANEL'S OBVIOUS RECOGNITION OF APPLICANT'S GOOD FAITH, APPLICANT DECIDED NOT TO APPEAL THE DECISION.  THE FORM U-6 FILED BY THE NATIONAL ASSOCIATION OF SECURITIES DEALERS, INC. IS MISLEADING IN THAT IT DOES NOT MENTION THAT THE CHARGE  AGAINST APPLICANT STATING THAT HE VIOLATED SEC RULE 15C3-1 WAS REMOVED BY ITS ENFORCEMENT DIVISION BEFORE THE HEARING EVEN  TOOK PLACE.  THE DECISION OF THE HEARING PANEL WAS THUS LIMITED TO ALLEGATIONS RELATED TO RULE 2110."
